Package: pakhom
Title: AI-Assisted Thematic Analysis with Methodology-as-Architecture
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: person(given = c("Abanoub", "J."), family = "Armanious",
    role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "armaniousabanoub@gmail.com",
    comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-7005-8297"))
Description: Conducts AI-assisted thematic analysis across three
    methodologically-distinct operating modes (reflexive scaffold, codebook
    collaborative, framework applied). Methodology is codified at the
    architectural level: the AI's role is shaped by the mode declared in
    the config, not by user discipline at the configuration level. Universal
    Tier-0 transparency requirements (quote provenance via a 4-step
    verification ladder, participant spread per theme, whole-corpus coverage
    assertion) are mandatory in every mode. Supports OpenAI and Anthropic
    providers, soft-lock and parent_run_id for auditable, comparable re-runs,
    methodology rules auto-injected into every model context, mid-pipeline
    researcher review (CSV or QDPX), QDPX export for QDA-software
    interoperability, AI decision audit trails (JSONL), reflexive memos as
    data with Markdown round-trip, framework specs (Theory of Planned
    Behavior, COM-B, Theoretical Domains Framework included as built-ins),
    and publication-quality HTML reports. Empirically motivated by Sarkar
    2024 (CACM, AI Should Challenge Not Obey), Jowsey et al. 2025 (PLOS
    One, the Frankenstein finding), and Braun and Clarke 2022 (reflexive
    thematic analysis). The package name 'pakhom' (Coptic for 'eagle')
    honors Saint Pachomius the Great (c. 292-348 CE), whose written Rule
    of communal discipline established the genre of methodology-as-written-
    document, of which this package is a digital descendant.
